From: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
Subject: [PATCH] net: fman: fix uninitialized onesCount in FM_PCD_HashTableSet

The onesCount local variable in FM_PCD_HashTableSet() is declared but
never initialized to zero before being incremented in the while loop
that counts set bits of the hash result mask. This causes onesCount
to start from whatever garbage value is on the kernel stack, producing
a wrong numOfSets value (1 << (garbage + actual_count)). The resulting
overflow cascades into invalid parameters for FM_PCD_MatchTableSet,
ultimately causing a kernel NULL pointer dereference.

Initialize onesCount = 0 to fix hash table creation on DPAA1 platforms.

Also initialize countOnes in IcHashIndexedCheckParams for the same
reason (cosmetic — that function also relies on incrementing from an
uninitialized value).

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
---
 .../freescale/sdk_fman/Peripherals/FM/Pcd/fm_cc.c      | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/Peripherals/FM/Pcd/fm_cc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/Peripherals/FM/Pcd/fm_cc.c
@@ -4059,7 +4059,7 @@ static t_Error IcHashIndexedCheckParams(
 {
     int         i;
     uint16_t    glblMask;
-    uint8_t     countOnes;
+    uint8_t     countOnes = 0;
     uint16_t    numOfKeys;
 
     glblMask = p_CcNodeParam->extractCcParams.extractNonHdr.icIndxMask;
@@ -7589,7 +7589,7 @@ t_Handle FM_PCD_HashTableSet(t_Handle h_
     t_FmPcdCcNode           *p_CcNodeHashTbl = NULL;
     t_Handle                h_MissStatsCounters = NULL;
     uint32_t                countMask;
-    uint8_t                 onesCount;
+    uint8_t                 onesCount = 0;
     uint16_t                numOfSets, numOfWays;
     int                     i;
     t_Error                 err;